description: From Dharug garrajung (“fishing line”), from the use made of the bark.

entries.meaning: (Australia) Any of a number of species of tree or shrub in the genus Brachychiton.
examples: My young friend, Master Keith McKeown, now finds this beetle under the stones about the roots of the kurrajong at Wagga, and also sheltering during the winter in the seed-pods on the trees.

entries.meaning: (Australia) A peanut tree, Sterculia quadrifida, native to eastern coastal Australia; a red- or orange-fruited kurrajong.
